    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-decision-01",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification bounds the hemolysis index predictions conservatively, and that the identified gaps are documented as epistemic uncertainties with defined remediation paths. The decision is conditional on completion of model-form uncertainty analysis and experimental repeatability studies prior to regulatory submission.",
